Gafargaon is a sub-district (upazila) in the Mymensingh District of Bangladesh. It is situated in the central part of the country. The region is known for its agricultural activities, and the economy is primarily based on agriculture. Gafargaon has a rural setting, with a significant portion of its population engaged in farming.
